ACT:
 Bombay Tenancy and Agricultural Lands Act, 1948, sections 2 (18), 4, 32F and G, scope of-Whether a limited owner of agricultural land governed by the Tenancy Act during his/her life time was entitled to lease the land, and is he or she did lease the land whether the tenant inducted by the holder of life estate could be said to be lawfully cultivating the land so as to acquire the status of a deemed tenant under section 4 of the Act and as a corollary would become a deemed purchaser on the tillers' day-Transfer of Property Act, section 13, section 76A and construction of the deed of settlement.
 
